			<div class="comment-body"><p>Thanks for this series!</p>
<p>Regarding a &#8220;zoom&#8221; effect &#8211; Avid has two confusingly similar in name affects.  &#8220;Pan and zoom&#8221; is the effect for stills, but &#8220;Pan and scan&#8221; does indeed do what you need for video.  You can keyframe zoom and position, and thus simulate camera moves to a degree&#8230;</p>
</div>

